1 (A) Incorporate the Prosperity 10,000 Program into the statewide plan for the SNAP Employ-
2 ment and Training Program;
3 (B) Seek federal reimbursement for 50 percent of the Prosperity 10,000 Program’s costs and for
4 other eligible activities as reported by the local workforce development boards;
5 (C) Refer individuals who receive supplemental nutrition assistance under ORS 411.806 to
6 411.845 to participate in the Prosperity 10,000 Program; and
7 (D) Distribute moneys received as reimbursement under subparagraph (B) of this paragraph to
8 local workforce development boards, not later than 60 days after the department receives an invoice
