11 Prosperity 10,000 Program.
12 (6) The State Workforce and Talent Development Board, in consultation with the Committee for
13 Continuous Improvement, shall:
14 (a) Oversee the progress of the Prosperity 10,000 Program;
15 (b) Ensure that program goals are met; and
16 (c) Identify areas for program improvement.
17 SECTION 2. ORS 660.385 is amended to read:
18 660.385. [(1)(a) Not later than 60 days following March 17, 2022, the Higher Education Coordi-
19 nating Commission shall distribute the funds specifically appropriated to the commission under section
20 13, chapter 28, Oregon Laws 2022, to local workforce development boards to administer the Prosperity
21 10,000 Program.]
22 (1)(a) The Higher Education Coordinating Commission shall distribute the funds specif-
23 ically appropriated by the Legislative Assembly for the purpose of administering the Pros-
24 perity 10,000 Program to local workforce development boards to carry out such purposes.
25 (b) The commission shall distribute all moneys received [from moneys made available under
26 sections 13 and 14, chapter 28, Oregon Laws 2022,] to local workforce development boards using the
27 same formula as required under the federal Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (29 U.S.C.
28 3101 et seq.) for the allocation of funds to local workforce development boards.
29 (2) Each local workforce development board shall compile data on the progress made toward
30 carrying out the Prosperity 10,000 Program. The boards shall prepare and submit a joint report that
31 includes data, disaggregated by race, gender and geography, to the commission and the State
32 Workforce and Talent Development Board no later than October 31 of each year, in the manner
33 provided in ORS 192.245.
